Since you need **three** themes, use the **ResourceDictionary swap** approach (`AppThemeBinding` only supports two).

## 1. Create theme dictionaries with matching keys

**Themes/LightTheme.xaml**
```xml
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
                    x:Class="MyApp.Themes.LightTheme">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackgroundColor">White</Color>
    <Color x:Key="PrimaryTextColor">#333333</Color>
    <Color x:Key="AccentColor">#2196F3</Color>
</ResourceDictionary>
```

**Themes/DarkTheme.xaml** ŌĆö same keys, dark values.

**Themes/HighContrastTheme.xaml** ŌĆö same keys, high-contrast values (e.g., `Black` background, `White` text, `Yellow` accent).

Each needs a code-behind calling `InitializeComponent()`:

```csharp
namespace MyApp.Themes;
public partial class LightTheme : ResourceDictionary
{
    public LightTheme() => InitializeComponent();
}
```

## 2. Bind UI with `DynamicResource`

```xml
<ContentPage BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource PageBackgroundColor}">
    <Label Text="Hello" TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryTextColor}" />
    <Button Text="Action" BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource AccentColor}" />
</ContentPage>
```

**Must** be `DynamicResource` ŌĆö `StaticResource` won't update at runtime.

## 3. Theme-switching helper

```csharp
public static class ThemeService
{
    public static void ApplyTheme(string themeName)
    {
        var mergedDictionaries = Application.Current!.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
        mergedDictionaries.Clear();
        mergedDictionaries.Add(themeName switch
        {
            "Dark"         => new DarkTheme(),
            "HighContrast" => new HighContrastTheme(),
            _              => new LightTheme()
        });

        // Persist the choice
        Preferences.Set("AppTheme", themeName);
    }
}
```

## 4. Settings page

```csharp
// In your settings page picker changed handler:
void OnThemePicked(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme(picker.SelectedItem.ToString());
}
```

## 5. Restore on startup (App constructor)

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme(Preferences.Get("AppTheme", "Light"));
}
```

## 6. Android ŌĆö prevent activity restart

Ensure `MainActivity` includes `ConfigChanges.UiMode`:

```csharp
[Activity(ConfigurationChanges = ConfigChanges.ScreenSize
                               | ConfigChanges.Orientation
                               | ConfigChanges.UiMode
                               | ConfigChanges.ScreenLayout
                               | ConfigChanges.SmallestScreenSize
                               | ConfigChanges.Density)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }
```

---

**Key rules:**
- Every `x:Key` must exist in **all three** dictionaries or you'll get silent fallbacks.
- Never use hardcoded colors on themed elements.
- CSS themes can't be swapped at runtime ŌĆö stick with ResourceDictionary.
